data.enText: all the people who live in a particular area, country, etc. when talked about as a group

data.chText: 当地社会对这些谋杀案感到震惊。
data.enText: The local community was shocked by the murders.

data.chText: 以社区为基地的保健工作人员
data.enText: health workers based in the community (= working with people in a local area)
the international community (= the countries of the world as a group)

data.chText: 社区与警方之间的良好关系
data.enText: good community relations with the police
community parks/libraries (= paid for by the local town/city)

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group of people who share the same religion, race, job, etc.

data.chText: 在伦敦的波兰侨民团体

data.enText: the feeling of sharing things and belonging to a group in the place where you live

data.chText: 这个镇上有一种强烈的社区意识。
data.enText: There is a strong sense of community in this town.
a group of plants and animals growing or living in the same place or environment

simple_means.memory_skill: com 共同 + mun 公共的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 公共状态 → 社会，社区

ex.chText: 这是当地西班牙人的一个社区。
ex.enText: Here is a local Spanish community.

ex.chText: 该地区有一种强烈的社区意识。
ex.enText: There is a strong sense of community in this area.

synonyms.bx: 指同住一地的人所构成的群体。

ex.chText: 他们访问了巴黎的一个艺术家聚居区。
ex.enText: They visited an artists' colony in Paris.

synonyms.bx: 指同住一地、具有某些相似处的群体，也指该群体的居住地。

ex.chText: 咖啡/嬉皮士/网络文化群体

synonyms.bx: 通常指共同生活、分享财物、分担职责的群体。

tr: (ecology) a group of interdependent organisms inhabiting the same region and interacting with each other
a group of people living in a particular local area
example: the team is drawn from all parts of the community

tr: a group of nations having common interests
example: they hoped to join the NATO community
they shared a community of possessions
the preachers and the bootleggers found they had a community of interests

value.def: The community is all the people who live in a particular area or place.

example.ex: He's well liked by people in the community...
example.tran: 社区的人都非常喜欢他。

example.ex: 'The community are getting impatient,' said a representative of the Residents' Association...
example.tran: “社区居民开始不耐烦了，”居民协会的一位代表说。

example.ex: The growth of such vigilante gangs has worried community leaders, police and politicians.
example.tran: 这类治安维持会成员组成的帮派的壮大让社区领袖、警察和政界人士十分担心。

value.tran: (同住一地的人所构成的)社区

value.def: A particular community is a group of people who are similar in some way.

example.ex: The police haven't really done anything for the black community in particular.
example.tran: 警方并未真正特意为黑人群体做什么。

value.def: Community is friendship between different people or groups, and a sense of having something in common.

example.ex: A supportive house for eight to ten older people, each with his or her own room, provides privacy and a sense of community...
example.tran: 一幢扶助性住宅可供8至10位老人居住，每个人都有自己单独的房间，在这里，他们既能独处，又有社区归属感。

example.ex: Two of our greatest strengths are diversity and community.
example.tran: 我们最大的两个优势是多样性和团体精神。

value.tran: (不同人士、团体之间的)友谊，伙伴关系

trans: 社区护理服务(让长期需要帮助者在家中接受医疗等)
社区中学(在英国除接收本校学生外亦向当地社区成人开放)
社区服务(自愿或因受法庭惩罚的无偿劳动)
住宅小区(四周有围墙或围栏，入口有门卫)

partsOfSpeech.dec: com 共同 + mun 公共的 + al …的 → 公共的
com 共同 + mun 公共的 + e → 大家一起说 → 商量，引申为大家的地方 → 公社
com 共同 + mun 公共的 + icate →〔大家〕交谈；使大家知道 → 交流；通知
com 共同 + mun 公共的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 公共状态 → 社会，社区
commun 共同 + ize …化 → 公社化 → 共产化
im 不 + mun 公共的 + ity 不给大家都有的〔权利〕→ 免除 → 能免除一般疾病的 → 免疫
im 不 + mun 公共的 + ize 使… → 不受大众〔的影响〕，能免除杂念的 → 使免疫；免除
muni 公共的 + cip 头 + al …的 → 公众之头 → 市政的
municipal 都市的，市政的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 市政当局
muni 公共的 + fic 做 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 做出来给大家 → 慷慨的
